# Tests: run only when warranted

**Do not run `npm test` (or integration tests) after every change.** Repeated full test runs waste the user's tokens, especially for low-risk edits.

## Skip tests (unless the user asks to run them)

- Renames (functions, types, files, agent names, strings)
- Comments, JSDoc, README, and other docs-only changes
- Import path updates with no logic change
- Formatting and cosmetic refactors with identical behavior

After these edits: summarize what changed and tell the user they can run `npm test` if they want verification.

## Run tests when it actually matters

- Logic, control flow, or API behavior changed
- User explicitly asks to run or fix tests
- User reports a test failure
- You are unsure a change is behavior-preserving (e.g. non-trivial refactor)

When you do run tests, prefer targeted checks when possible instead of the full suite every time.
